  <static seed="1264" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions90.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{t}{t+5}-\frac{t+30}{t^{2}+5t}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{t-6}{t}, t\ne -5</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{t}{t+5}-\frac{t+30}{t^{2}+5t}} 
      \amp = {\frac{t}{t+5}}-\frac{{t+30}}{t(t+5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{t \cdot t}{({t+5}) \cdot t}-\frac{{t+30}}{t(t+5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{t^{2}}{t(t+5)}-\frac{{t+30}}{t(t+5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{t^{2}-({t+30})}{t(t+5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{t^{2}-t-30}}{t(t+5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{(t+5)(t - 6)}{t(t+5)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t-6}{t}, t\ne -5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{t+5}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {-5}</m>.</p>
</solution>
